}}'''Corperryale "Manny" Harris''' (born September 21, 1989) is a sophomore [[guard (basketball)|guard]] for the [[Michigan Wolverines men's basketball]] team.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chicagotribune.com/sports/college/northwestern/chi-081026-michigan-basketball-big-ten,0,1668328.story|title=Michigan preview|accessdate=2008-11-02|date=2008-10-26|work=[[Chicago Tribune]]}}</ref>  Harris played high school basketball for [[Redford High School]] in {{city-state|Detroit|Michigan}} where he was a two-time All-State first team selection and a [[Mr. Basketball of Michigan]] winner.<ref name=HRATSTaAFT>{{cite web|url=http://www.mgoblue.com/basketball-m/article.aspx?id=111528|title=Harris Receives All-Big Ten Second Team and All-Freshman Team|accessdate=2008-11-02|date=2008-03-10|publisher=University of Michigan & Host Interactive}}</ref><ref name=MH*/>  He is a [[2008-09 NCAA Division I men's basketball season|2008&ndash;09]] first team pre-season All-Big Ten player and both a [[2007-08 NCAA Division I men's basketball season|2007&ndash;08]] second team pre-season and post season All-[[Big Ten Conference]] selection.<ref name=BTMP&AC>{{cite web|url=http://www.collegehoopsnet.com/big-ten-media-poll-amp-allconference-133667|title=Big Ten Media Poll & All-Conference|accessdate=2008-11-01|date=2008-10-29|publisher=Collegehoops.net}}</ref>  He entered his sophomore season as the leading returning scorer in the Big Ten and as the conferences top rated [[NBA Draft]] prospect.<ref name=TNDPitB1>{{cite web|url=http://www.draftexpress.com/article/Top-NBA-Draft-Prospects-in-the-Big-10--Part-One-1-5--3000/|title=Top NBA Draft Prospects in the Big 10 (Part One: #1-5)|accessdate=2008-11-03|date=2008-09-10|prospect=DraftExpress LLC|author=Givony, Jonathan}}</ref>  He is the 2008&ndash;09 Big Ten Conference scoring average leader.<ref name=2BTCMBLs/>

==High School==
Born in {{city-state|Detroit|Michigan}}, Harris was an [[Associated Press]] Class A All-State first team selection in both 2006 and 2007.<ref name=MH*>{{cite web|url=http://www.mgoblue.com/basketball-m/playerbio.aspx?id=68736|title=Manny Harris*|accessdate=2008-11-03|publisher=University of Michigan & Host Interactive}}</ref> Harris was selected as the 2007 Mr. Basketball of Michigan.  That season he led the Redford Huskies to the [[Michigan High School Athletic Association]] Class A championship game, which it lost to [[Saginaw High School]].  During his high school basketball career, he became the first player to start for three consecutive Detroit Public School League Champions since [[Jalen Rose]] and [[Voshon Lenard]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.detroitpslbasketball.com/?page_id=147|title=Mr. Basketball Winners |accessdate=2008-11-02|publisher=Detroit PSL Basketball}}</ref>  Harris once posted 52 [[Point (basketball)|points]] and 15 [[rebound (basketball)|rebounds]] in a high school basketball game.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://michigan.rivals.com/content.asp?CID=621483|title=Manny Harris scores 52 in Redford win|accessdate=2008-11-11|date=2006-12-20|publisher=STATS LLC|work=[[Rivals.com]]|author=Balas, Chris}}</ref>  During his 2006&ndash;07 senior season, he averaged 33.5 points, 11.5 rebounds and 5.5 [[assist (basketball)|assists]].<ref name=MH*/>  Harris was highly recruited receiving offers from the [[Tennessee Volunteers men's basketball|Tennessee Volunteers]], [[UCLA Bruins men's basketball|UCLA Bruins]], [[Wisconsin Badgers men's basketball|Wisconsin Badgers]], George Washington Colonials, and [[Indiana Hoosiers men's basketball]] teams.<ref name=CHR>{{cite web|url=http://www.rivals.com/viewprospect.asp?Sport=2&pr_key=49907|title=Corperryale Harris|accessdate=2008-12-03|publisher=[[Rivals.com]]}}</ref>  He was ranked by [[Rivals.com]] as the #6 [[shooting guard]] in the country in the 2007 high school class.<ref name=CHR/>  [[Scout.com]] ranked him as the twelfth best shooting guard.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://michigan.scout.com/a.z?s=162&p=8&c=1&nid=1968121|title=Corperryale Harris|accessdate=2008-12-03|publisher=GoBlueWolverine.com and [[Scout.com]]}}</ref>  [[ESPN]] ranked him #7, but they listed him as a [[point guard]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://insider.espn.go.com/ncb/recruiting/tracker/player?recruitId=43496&season=2007&action=login&appRedirect=http%3a%2f%2finsider.espn.go.com%2fncb%2frecruiting%2ftracker%2fplayer%3frecruitId%3d43496%26season%3d2007|title=Corperryale "Manny" Harris | Point Guard
|accessdate=2008-12-03|publisher=ESPN Internet Ventures}}</ref>  When Michigan announced that they were replacing [[Tommy Amaker]] with [[John Beilein]] as [[head coach]], Harris was not sure if he would honor his signed [[letter of intent]], but when Michigan re-signed assistant coach Mike Jackson, he decided to attend to the [[University of Michigan]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.michigansportscenter.com/2007/04/manny-harris-to-stay-with-michigan.html|title=Manny Harris to Stay with Michigan!|accessdate=2008-11-02|date=2007-04-11|publisher=Michigan Sports Center}}</ref>

