==College==
[[Image:20071208 Manny Harris brings the ball upcourt against Duke.jpg|thumb|left|Harris [[dribble]]s the ball upcourt against [[Duke Blue Devils men's basketball|Duke]] (2007-12-08)]]
Prior to the 2007&ndash;08 basketball season, he was selected as a second team pre-season All-[[Big Ten Conference]] selection.<ref name=BTMP&AC/> After the 2007&ndash;08 NCAA basketball season, Harris was selected as a second team All-Big Ten Conference selection and placed second to [[Eric Gordon]] in the Freshman of the Year balloting, which earned him an All-Freshman team selection.  He led the Wolverines in scoring (16.4), assists (2.8), [[steal (basketball)|steals]] (1.5), minutes (32.9) and [[free throw]] percentage (82.0).<ref name=HRATSTaAFT/>  Among his highlights during the season were being named to the [[Great Alaska Shootout]] tournament team, becoming the fourth U-M freshman to score over 500 points in first season (516), and setting the U-M freshman record for [[free throw]]s made in a season while playing at least 20&nbsp;minutes and starting every game.<ref name=MH*/>

As a 2008&ndash;09 first team pre-season All-Big Ten player, he is the first Wolverine to earn the honor since [[Daniel Horton]] in 2004.<ref name=HnhtlutATs>{{cite web|url=http://www.michigandaily.com/content/2008-10-29/mens-basketball-notebook|title=Harris now has to live up to All-Preseason Team selection|accessdate=2008-11-06|date=2008-10-28|publisher=[[University of Michigan]]|work=[[The Michigan Daily]]|author=Prosperi, Alex}}</ref>  Although he is the leading returning scorer and top draft prospect,<ref name=TNDPitB1/> [[Purdue Boilermakers men's basketball|Purdue]]'s [[Robbie Hummel]] was named Big Ten Preseason Player of the Year.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ohiostatebuckeyes.com/pdf4/149313.pdf?ATCLID=1610476&SPID=10421&DB_OEM_ID=17300&SPSID=87813|title=Purdue's Robbie Hummel Tabbed As Big Ten Preseason Player of the Year|accessdate=2008-11-06|date=2008-10-26|publisher=Big Ten Conference|author=Sadler, LaTonya}}</ref>  Preseason All-Big Ten status has not always led to regular season honors.  In both 2005 and 2007, only two preseason selections made the regular season team.<ref name=HnhtlutATs/>  Harris opened the [[2008-09 Michigan Wolverines men's basketball team|2008-09 Michigan Wolverines men's basketball season]] with a career-high 30 points in a 77&ndash;55 victory over [[Michigan Tech]] on November 11.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://scores.espn.go.com/ncb/recap?gameId=283160130|title=Harris' career-high 30 points carry Michigan past Michigan Tech|accessdate=2008-11-12|date=2008-11-11|publisher=ESPN Internet Ventures}}</ref>  The following night in the second game of the Coaches vs. cancer classic, Harris nearly posted a [[triple double]] when he posted 26 points, and career-highs with 10 rebounds and 8 assists in a 76&ndash;56 win against [[Northeastern University]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sports.espn.go.com/ncb/recap?gameId=283170130|title=Harris leads Michigan to semifinals of Coaches vs. Cancer tournament|accessdate=2008-11-13|date=2008-11-12|publisher=ESPN Internet Ventures}}</ref>  At the end of November, while his team had a 5&ndash;1 record, Harris led the team in points, rebounds, assists, free throw percentage and steals.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sports.espn.go.com/ncb/teams/stats?teamId=130|title=Michigan Wolverines Statistics - 2008-09|accessdate=2008-12-03|publisher=ESPN Internet Ventures}}</ref>  He is the Big Ten Conference leader in scoring and free throws made.<ref name=2BTCMBLs>{{cite web|url=http://sports.espn.go.com/ncb/leaders?groupId=7&cat=scoring&sort=AVG&seasonYear=2009|title=2008-2009 Big Ten Conference Men's Basketball Leaders (scoring)|accessdate=2008-12-03|publisher=ESPN Internet Ventures}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://sports.espn.go.com/ncb/leaders?cat=ft&type=1&groupId=7&seasonType=2&seasonYear=2009|title=2008-2009 Big Ten Conference Men's Basketball Leaders (free throws)|accessdate=2008-12-03|publisher=ESPN Internet Ventures}}</ref>

==Personal==
His name, Corperryale, is a combination of the names of his [[cousin]] (Corrine), an uncle (Perry) and the "ale" of his immediate siblings -- Janelle, Jerrelle and Al.  He has a total of nine brothers and sisters and is the son of Merrick (Harris-Carter) and James Carter.<ref name=MH*/>

